# Docker Volumes

## Q11: Create and Use a Named Volume

```bash
docker volume create mydata

docker run -it --name mycontainer \
-v mydata:/app/data \
ubuntu bash
```

Inside container:

```bash
echo "Persistent data" > /app/data/file.txt
```

---

## Q12: Test Data Persistence

```bash
docker stop container1
docker rm container1
```

Run another container with the same volume:

```bash
docker run -it --name container2 -v mydata:/app/data ubuntu bash
```

Check file:

```bash
cat /app/data/file.txt
```

The file still exists because volumes store data permanently.

